(943, 62, 'profiles_5_biography', '<div class="biography">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nHer experience covers corporate reputation, crisis management and special situations alongside a wide range of capital market communications including IPOs, secondary fundraisings, placings, M&amp;A, restructurings and re-financings as well as financial calendar related IR and media relations campaigns.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nAmongst her high profile successful M&amp;A transactions, Ginny has advised Hyder on its two sided bid defence from Arcadis and Nippon Koei and May Gurney plc on its defence from Costain and Kier.  High profile international campaigns she has led include advising ABB on its US acquisitions of Thomas &amp; Betts and Baldor Inc., Colfax on its US$1.2bn bid for Charter and Ferrovial’s £10.4bn takeover of BAA.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nGinny previously was a co-founder of Citigate Dewe Rogerson and worked there from 1988 to 2014. During this period she has advised a wide range of corporates across the industrials, support services and technology sectors, with clients such as VT Group plc, Babcock, Shanks, Indra Sistemas, Alere and Pace Micro Technology plc.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nPrior to entering financial communications, Ginny worked in corporate finance at N.M.Rothschild and Bankers Trust.\r\n\r\nEmail: <a href="mailto:ginny.pulbrook@camarco.co.uk">ginny.pulbrook@camarco.co.uk</a>\r\n\r\nDirect no: 020 3757 4992\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>'),
